{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a7a20b9c-8848-42e8-a10a-a2c6824095ba","content":"Set these environment variables before launching your app:\n\n```bash\n# Enable crash dumps\nexport DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1\n\n# Full dump (type 4). Options: 1=Normal, 2=WithHeap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4\n\n# Output path (%d = PID, %t = timestamp)\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName=/var/dumps/coredump.%d.%t.dmp\n```\n\nMake sure the target directory exists and is writable:\n\n```bash\nsudo mkdir -p /var/dumps\nsudo chmod 1777 /var/dumps\n```\n\n**Verify the configuration:**\n\n```bash\n# 1. Confirm the env vars are set\nenv | grep DOTNET_Dbg\n\n# 2. Simulate a crash to test (in a non-production context)\ndotnet run &\nkill -SIGABRT $!\n\n# 3. Check that a dump was written\nls -lh /var/dumps/\n```\n\n> **Note:** The `DOTNET_` prefix replaced the older `COMPlus_` prefix starting in .NET 6. Both still work, but `DOTNET_` is preferred for .NET 10.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e15aa06e-4846-483c-800c-766ce33e7e0f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about configuring automatic crash dump collection for a .NET 10 CoreCLR application running on Linux. This is a knowledge question about .NET runtime configuration, not a code change task. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":377,"requestId":"D80D:13B160:5F9A623:678005D:69FBEFE0"},"id":"fd0b464e-eae6-49bf-9a9c-3311568e97e7","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:50:32.920Z","parentId":"34d5fdfd-b4c2-4d8e-8a12-44de40d193e2"}
